  "courseOverview": {
    "introduction": "Ray tracing is a powerful rendering technique used in computer graphics to create incredibly realistic images. It simulates the way light travels in the real world, allowing for accurate lighting effects and shadows.",
    "courseStructure": "This course is designed to take you on a journey from the fundamentals of ray tracing to creating your own stunning images. We will build your knowledge step-by-step, ensuring a solid understanding of the core concepts. This beginner-friendly course offers 13 lectures on the basics and 8 coding practices to help you create impressive images.",
    "learningLanguage": "The course utilizes Python for all exercises. This choice makes the course accessible to a wider audience, even those with no prior programming experience. Python's clear syntax and extensive libraries make it a perfect language for learning ray tracing.",
    "weeklyStructure": "The course material is divided into manageable 8-week practices. Each week will introduce new concepts and provide hands-on exercises to solidify your understanding.",
    "courseOutline": "This course offers a comprehensive ray tracing curriculum, starting with foundational concepts and progressing to intermediate and advanced topics. Each step-by-step lesson builds on the previous one, ensuring a smooth learning curve for beginners and a chance for more experienced learners to deepen their knowledge and expand their skills.",
    "audience": "The course is provided to undergraduate students of Computer Science program, Faculty of Science, Kasetsart University."
  },
